This is the one I believe could become Pantheon’s defining contribution.

Most knowledge systems optimize for storage.

Some optimize for retrieval.

A few optimize for search.

Very few optimize for reconstruction.

If Pantheon can do this well, it becomes much more than a repository—it becomes a test of whether understanding has actually been transmitted.

