The Human Test

The strongest reconstruction is not repetition.

It is creation.

If someone learns a concept…

builds something genuinely new…

and remains faithful to its governing invariants…

then reconstruction has succeeded.

Innovation becomes evidence of understanding.

⸻

Repository-Wide Reconstruction

The repository itself should be reconstructible.

Imagine the repository is destroyed.

Only three artifacts survive.

Can Pantheon be rebuilt?

If not…

the core is insufficiently compressed.

