The Reconstruction Oath

We preserve meaning before wording.

We preserve relationships before categories.

We preserve understanding before memory.

We preserve reconstruction before replication.

We welcome translation.

We welcome compression.

We welcome reinterpretation that preserves invariant structure.

We build so that understanding survives us.

